 \"description\": \"As a user, I want the agent to discover tools from MCP servers and make them available for use.\",\n285:        \"Call tools/list on each server to get tool definitions\",\n286:        \"Convert MCP tools to ToolPort interface and register in ToolRegistry\",\n287:        \"MCP tool execution forwards via tools/call to the corresponding server\",\n288:        \"Server disconnect auto-removes its tools from registry\",\n310:        \"ComputerUseLifecycle trait with: before_tool_call(), after_turn_cleanup(), on_interrupt_cleanup()\",\n337:        \"route_input(): slash command routing (e.g. /brief switches mode); precedence is deterministic\",\n359:      \"title\": \"Mode-aware tool visibility\",\n360:      \"description\": \"As a user, I want tool visibility to change based on the current assistant mode so that irrelevant tools are hidden.\",\n362:        \"Each mode defines a tool allowlist\",\n364:        \"Brief mode hides high-risk tools\",\n373:      \"notes\": \"Add definitions_for_mode(mode) method to ToolRegistry. Wire into agent loop's tool list construction.\",\n661:      \"description\": \"As a user, I want the coordinator agent to spawn and manage worker agents via tools.\",\n675:      \"notes\": \"Extend existing crates/tools/src/spawn_agent.rs. Add TaskStopTool. Wire notification routing in bootstrap.\",\n727:        \"Error logs include structured context (session_id, provider, tool_name)\",\n736:      \"notes\": \"Add tracing spans to application, provider, tools, mcp-runtime, remote-runtime. Add correlation ID to AppState or pass via tracing context.\",\n794:        \"Introduce a new command `ccode tui` that boots an event loop and full-screen terminal mode\",\n804:      \"notes\": \"Create `crates/cli/src/cmd/tui.rs` and wire command in clap definitions. Add a small `ui` module for draw loop and terminal setup/teardown guards.\",\n814:      \"title\": \"Ratatui streaming renderer for assistant and tool events\",\n815:      \"description\": \"As a user, I want streaming model output and tool execution events rendered incrementally in the TUI so that I can follow progress in real time.\",\n863:      \"description\": \"As a user, I want a clear in-TUI tool approval modal so that I can safely approve or deny tool executions without leaving full-screen mode.\",\n865:        \"When a tool requires confirmation, show a modal with tool name, parameter summary, and risk level\",\n876:      \"notes\": \"Share confirmation policy/state with existing command path to avoid duplicated business logic. TUI layer should only handle rendering + key mapping.\",\n891:        \"Supports stop action for running tasks via existing stop tool path\",\n971:        \"Integration test: tool use flow — request with tools → response with tool_use → follow-up with tool_result\",\n977:        \"Agent loop test: agent loop can alternate between complete() and tool execution using only Canonical types\",\n1025:        \"Integration test: MCP server registration + tool dispatch happy path\",\n1026:        \"Integration test: interrupt during tool call triggers cleanup once\",\n1052:        \"Integration test: tool visibility changes when mode switches\",\n1053:        \"CLI behavior test: tool visibility and prompt mode branch are correct\",\n1076:        \"Integration test: KAIROS/BRIEF/CHANNELS combinations produce expected tool visibility\",\n1081:        \"CLI behavior test: mode switch via /brief command works end-to-end\",\n1157:        \"CLI behavior test: bare command usage path returns expected guidance\",\n1159:        \"CLI behavior test: stop command clears local active markers and session URL state\",\n1235:        \"Spec QA checklist from acceptance-playbook.md encoded as verification script or test\",\n1256:      \"id\": \"US-047\",\n1257:      \"title\": \"Acceptance-spec architecture and functional parity validation\",\n1258:      \"description\": \"As a developer, I want architecture acceptance criteria from